Cron is a system service that will run in the background and check for schedualed tasks & execute them.
The schedualed tasks are stored in a file called crontab which cron will be scanning every minute.
Each user has their one crontab which are stored in the following folder: /var/spool/cron/crontabs/
The systems crontab file is found in the following folder: /etc/crontab
The task are written in scripts and executables. They are then split up into hourly-, daily-, weekly and monthly task folders.
The system tasks are mainly created by installed applications.
